  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 650 mg
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Drain @corn{1%unit}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1%unit} into strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1%unit}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add corn and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and lightly charred in spots, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Cover pan if corn begins to pop!

Turn off heat; transfer corn to a #small bowl{}. Stir in @fresh red salsa{4%ounce}; set aside until ready to serve.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for corn over medium-high heat. Add chicken, green pepper, onion, @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @cumin{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are just beginning to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Lower heat if chicken and veggies begin to brown too quickly.

> Save remaining cumin for another use.

Add 1/4 cup water and @butter{1%tablespoon} (1/2 cup water and 2 TBSP butter for 4). Cook, stirring frequently, until chicken is cooked through and sauce has slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Place @sour cream{1 1/2%tablespoon} in a second small bowl. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{} and top with chicken and veggies. Top with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and corn salsa. Drizzle crema over everything and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.